@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "NixNext" where you want
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed.

NOTE: I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that NixNext runs fine
      on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with a
      68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  To play, click on any tile; all tiles located next on the same
row and column as the clicked tile will blow-up. The clicked tile
as well as tiles that are of a different type will reappear where
they were located. However, if one or more tile of the same type
are next to the clicked tile, they will be removed and you will get
points according to the number of tiles that are of the same type,
as shown below:

2 tiles: 1 point
3 tiles: 4 points
4 tiles: 16 points
5 tiles: 64 points

  When tiles are removed, new tiles will appear on the game board.
The game starts with 3 types of tiles, as the game progresses, new
types of tiles are added from time to time.

  The game continues until there are no tiles of the same type that
are located next to each other.

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

